
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Enquire_Now";
}
<section>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6 ConnectingMLSI">
                <div class="Inn">
                    <h3 class="header3">Connecting with MLSI</h3>
                    <p>
                        The Admission Team advises that parents seeking School admission
                        for their child in the school to schedule an appointment either
                        by writing to us or initiate and complete online, 'Enquiry Form'
                        given in this page. These tours are organised by prior
                        appointment only.
                    </p>
                    <h5 class="header5 mb-4">Contact Details for School Admission Enquiry Form.</h5>
                    <div class="social-mail-links">
                        <p>
                            <img src="https://mlsi.in/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/contact-30x30.png" alt="" />
                            Call us @@+91 9930441459 / +91 9769330319
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <img src="https://mlsi.in/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/email.png" alt="" />
                            <a style="color: #1c62ad !important;" href="mailto:admission@mlsi.in">admission@mlsi.in</a>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <img src="https://mlsi.in/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/tweet.png" alt="" />
                            Twitter - @@mlsi_school
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <img src="https://mlsi.in/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/insta.png" alt="" />
                            Instagram - @@mlsi_school
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <img src="https://mlsi.in/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/facebook.png" alt="" />
                            Facebook - @@mountliteraschoolinternational
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <img src="https://mlsi.in/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/youtube.png" alt="" />
                            Youtube - youtube.com/mlsi_school
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="EnquiryForm">
                    <h4 class="header4 text-center mt-0 mb-4">
                        School Admission Enquiry Form
                    </h4>
                    <form name="EnquiryForm">
                        <div class="Inputgroup mt-0">
                            <input type="text" required />
                            <label>Parent's Name</label>
                            <span class="inputbar"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="Inputgroup">
                            <input type="text" required />
                            <label>Student's Name</label>
                            <span class="inputbar"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="Inputgroup">
                            <input type="email" required />
                            <label>Student Age</label>
                            <span class="inputbar"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="Inputgroup">
                            <input type="text">
                            <label>Mobile No</label>
                            <span class="inputbar"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="Inputgroup">
                            <input type="text" required />
                            <label>Enter a valid email address</label>
                            <span class="inputbar"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="Inputgroup">
                            <select name="grade" id="grade" type="text" required>
                                <option value="" selected="selected"></option>
                                <option value="Playgroup">Playgroup</option>
                                <option value="Nursery">Nursery</option>
                                <option value="Junior KG">Junior KG</option>
                                <option value="Senior KG">Senior KG</option>
                                <option value="Class I">Class I</option>
                                <option value="Class II">Class II</option>
                                <option value="Class III">Class III</option>
                                <option value="Class IV">Class IV</option>
                                <option value="Class V">Class V</option>
                                <option value="Class VI">Class VI</option>
                                <option value="Class VII">Class VII</option>
                                <option value="Class VII">Class VIII</option>
                                <option value="Class IX">Class IX</option>
                                <option value="Class X">Class X</option>
                                <option value="Class XI">Class XI</option>
                            </select>
                            <label>Enrollment In</label>
                            <span class="inputbar"></span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="row mt-3">
                            <div class="col-6 form-group">
                                <span style="background-color: lightgreen; padding: 10px 15px; font-size: 1.5rem; display: inline-block;">knn3fu</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-6 form-group">
                                <input class="form-control" type="text" />
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="mt-4">
                            <label><span class="mandatory">*</span>Would you like to receive updates regarding MLSI.</label>
                            <div>
                                <label class="radiobtn mr-3 mb-0">
                                    <input type="radio" name="MLSI" />
                                    <i></i><span>Yes</span>
                                </label>
                                <label class="radiobtn mb-0">
                                    <input type="radio" name="MLSI" />
                                    <i></i><span>No</span>
                                </label>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-center mt-4">
                            <button class="btn btn-lg btn-first btn-rounded">Submit</button>
                        </div>
                    </form>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>
            Mount Litera School International (MLSI) is a future-ready International Baccalaureate Continuum School. Authorised by the International Baccalaureate Organization to offer the Primary Years Programme (PYP), Middle Years Programme (MYP), and Diploma Programme (DP), MLSI is one of the few IB Continuum schools in Mumbai. It is centrally located in the plush locality, Bandra Kurla Complex (BKC).
        </p>
        <p>
            MLSI provides best-in-class learning to its students, thanks to its excellent infrastructure, internationally acclaimed head of school, IB-trained academic team, and innovative and holistic teaching methodologies. We assist your child in not only identifying but also acquiring critical 'life skills' that will assist them in becoming excellent communicators. Our IB programs help them to become creative thinkers, confident risk takers, highly knowledgeable, and well-balanced citizens.
        </p>
        <div class="InsideBlock" id="OurVision">
            <div class="InsideBlockHeader">
                Our Vision
            </div>
            <div class="InsideBlockBody">
                <p>
                    Mount Litera School International is a co-educational day school that provides an excellent education through a comprehensive curriculum. This is achieved in a friendly family atmosphere that nurtures a community feeling in which all students' emotional, physical, creative, and intellectual needs are met within an international community.
                </p>
                <ul class="checklist">
                    <li>
                        A successful transition from primary to secondary school.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        A team of highly skilled and committed teachers dedicated to instilling a lifelong love of learning and stimulating intellectual curiosity; fostering a culture of creativity; and developing and nurturing critical thinkers, problem solvers, decision makers, responsible risk takers, and effective communicators.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        A versatile, dynamic, and balanced inquiry-based curriculum [International Baccalaureate] in which involvement in extracurricular activities is valued equally to academic achievement.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Providing challenging learning opportunities both in and out of the classroom, resulting in self-assured, focused, disciplined, well-balanced, and enterprising young men and women who are ready to take their place and make their mark in modern society.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Within the context of a friendly and welcoming international community, traditional values such as courtesy, honesty, tolerance, and mutual respect are taught in a structured and purposeful manner.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Individual attention is provided in small class sizes in order to maximise opportunities for a variety of teaching and learning styles.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        A set up in which close and effective collaborations between teachers, support staff, and parents ensure that every child admitted benefits from the education provided.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        We provide a welcoming atmosphere in which diversity is celebrated and traditional values such as tolerance and mutual respect are practised.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="InsideBlock" id="OurSkill">
            <div class="InsideBlockHeader">
                Our Skill
            </div>
            <div class="InsideBlockBody">
                <ul class="checklist">
                    <li>
                        Develop into independent critical thinkers and active members of a global society.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Face life head on and live it in ways that require courage, generosity, imagination, principle, and resolve.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Acquire the knowledge, skills, and abilities required to set and achieve their own goals in order to become better leaders and guardians of the world of tomorrow.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="InsideBlock" id="OurObjectives">
            <div class="InsideBlockHeader">
                Our Objectives
            </div>
            <div class="InsideBlockBody">
                <ul class="checklist">
                    <li>
                        Establish a setting in which there is a shared enthusiasm for learning, teaching, achieving, and being together.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Appoint the best leaders, teachers, and support staff, and ensure that they receive ongoing professional development training.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Consider individual students' and staff's learning needs and personal development, as well as their right to the best education possible.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        We should value everyone and expect them to outperform their current expectations; we should raise the bar for what can be accomplished individually and collectively; and we should broaden our educational opportunities and broaden our horizons.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Partnering with our students' families, other local schools, institutions, and the larger community is essential.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Improve standards by focusing on the fundamental concepts, such as literacy, numeracy, science, and ICT.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Introduce the best new educational ideas and practices that are helping to raise standards.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    Guide students' development into self-assured young adults capable of positively contributing to the community and living full lives.
                </p>
                <p class="m-0">
                    To provide buildings and amenities that will proceed to enhance the quality of experience for students and staff, as well as our ability to provide 21st-century learning and instruction.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="InsideBlock" id="OurMission">
            <div class="InsideBlockHeader">
                Our Mission
            </div>
            <div class="InsideBlockBody">
                Mount Litera School International will provide students with a happy and secure environment in which to learn and grow socially. Our mission is to aspire for the best teaching and learning in order to ensure that all students achieve the highest academic standards possible while also being prepared to take their place as global citizens. We will aim to instil in them a love of learning, character integrity, and confidence in their ability to move confidently into the future, and an awareness of both the needs of others and their responsibilities to them, regardless of class, creed, or culture. Through intercultural understanding and respect, the International Baccalaureate Organization aims to create inquiring, competent, and caring youth who will contribute to the creation of a better and more peaceful world. The IBO joins forces with schools, governments, and international organisations to create challenging international education programmes and rigorous assessment. These programmes encourage students all over the world to become active, empathetic, lifelong learners who recognise that other people, despite their differences, can also be correct.
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>
